claim.claim-text:
6. A method comprising: 
receiving a request to transfer content to a customer; 
retrieving encrypted content corresponding to the requested content, the encrypted content being encrypted by a title key; 
obtaining a customer identifier (I.D.) associated with the customer; and 
binding the requested content to the customer I.D. by using the customer I.D. to encrypt the title key.

19. A machine-readable medium having stored thereon data representing sequences of instructions, the sequences of instructions which, when executed by a processor, cause the processor to perform the following: 
receive a request to transfer content to a customer; 
retrieve encrypted content corresponding to the requested content, the encrypted content being encrypted by a title key; 
obtain a customer identifier (I.D.) associated with the customer; and 
bind the requested content to the customer I.D. by using the customer I.D. to encrypt the title key.
